So they describe the same phrase, both in English, both in the Western culture, describe

11:15.720 --> 11:22.160
two sides for opposite outcomes of the same event.

11:22.160 --> 11:27.320
So idioms are obviously another source of misunderstanding.

11:27.320 --> 11:33.680
So phrases like, there's more than one way to skin a cat, which means there's more than

